        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 2:56AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 256 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Fairpoint, or 36 miles northeast of Sturgis,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Union Center, Plainview, Enning, Fairpoint, Marcus, White Owl,
Stoneville, and Red Owl.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
